      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Nothing is known of Charles Baldwin other than what can be gleaned from the collection.  He was a resident of Onondaga County, served in the United States Army in several capacities including as aide-de-camp to General John Ellis of the 5th New York Division, 27th Brigade, and was a Master of the Court of Chancery of the State of New York.</p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Charles Baldwin Collection</emph> is a small collection of documents relating to Charles Baldwin of Onondaga County.  Most pertain to his military service.  The documents include regimental orders.</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
